OL,6,FA woman from affected by state pension
OL,7,Fchanges says isn't enough.
OL,9,FLiz Latham is among a group of women
OL,10,Fborn in the 1950s known as "women"
OL,11,F(Women Against State Pension
OL,12,FInequality), who say the rise in the
OL,13,Fstate pension age in 1995 led them to
OL,14,Fsuffer financially.
OL,16,FThe Parliamentary and Health Service
OL,17,FOmbudsman says the Department for Work
OL,18,Fand Pensions (DWP) failed to
OL,19,Fadequately communicate changes to
OL,20,Fwomen's state pension age, and that
OL,21,Fthose affected are owed compensation.
